ary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Much altered English vernacular form of the Late Latin name <i>Aegidius</i>, from Greek <i>Aigidios</i> (a derivative of <i>aigidion</i> ‘kid, young goat’), via Old French <i>Gide</i>. It was the name of an 8th‐century saint who, according to tradition, was an Athenian citizen who fled to Provence because he could not cope with the fame and adulation caused by his power to work miracles, in particular by healing the lame and crippled. This was not a particularly common name in the Middle Ages and its use seems to have been confined to certain families and localities."],"variants":[{"name":"Gyles","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Giles ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Giles de Fulbourne was born in 1270, in Fulbourn, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Stephen de Fulbourne and Mrs Stephen de Fulburne. He had at least 1 daughter with Unkown Fullbourn. He died in 1353, at the age of 83."},"et":{"1270–1353":"1270–1353","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1274–Female":"1274–Surnud","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1248–Male":"1248–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1315":"1315","1248":"1248","about 1315":"umbes 1315","1353":"1353","about 1269":"umbes 1269","1274":"1274","1270":"1270","Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Fulbourn, Cambridge, England":"Fulbourn, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fulbourne, Cambridgeshire, England":"Fulbourn, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1270–1353":"1270–1353","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1274–Female":"1274–Kuollut","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1248–Male":"1248–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1315":"1315","1248":"1248","about 1315":"noin 1315","1353":"1353","about 1269":"noin 1269","1274":"1274","1270":"1270","Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Fulbourn, Cambridge, England":"Fulbourn, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fulbourne, Cambridgeshire, England":"Fulbourn, Cambridgeshire, Englan